The paper proposes a metric for testing models learned from neural networks in autonomous systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of weights and scenarios, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). The application of the proposed metric is demonstrated in a visual object detection unit, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO).
